The paper proposes a method for discovering and monitoring linked data sources on the Web using search engines. This involves keyword discovery, search engine utilization, and link analysis. The paper is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves search engine usage and discovery of relevant keywords. It is also relevant to databases (cs.DB) as it deals with discovering and monitoring data sources. Additionally, the paper involves link analysis, which is relevant to both web search and data mining (cs.DL). The paper also deals with linked data, which is a topic in web science (cs.WEB). Finally, the paper involves the development of a new SPARQL endpoint crawler, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
